QUE
===
#include "que.h"
Structures: Que, QueElem

  Boolean queEmpty(Que): whether the queue is empty
  void queInit(Que): initialize an empty queue
  void queRemove(QueElem*): remove an element from its queue
  QueElem queGet(Que): get front element from queue (atomic)
  void quePut(Que, QueElem): add element to end of queue (atomic)
  void QueiPut(Que, QueElem): add element to end of queue (inatomic)

Note:
  - Que is actually pointer to QueElem
  - The actual content of a queue element can be retrieve from QueElem
    since the relative position of QueElem within the content structure
    is known. 


SEMA
====
#include "sema.h"
Structures: SemaObj, SemaLink, SemaMan
Constant: WAIT_FOREVER

void semaInit(): to initialize SEMA module

Binary semaphore:
  SemaMan semaBCreate(SemaBinary)
  void semaBGive(SemaMan)
  Boolean semaBTake(SemaMan, Uint32)

Counting semaphore:
  SemaMan semaCreate(Int32): create semaphore and initialize count
  void semaGive(SemaMan): signal sempahore
  Boolean semaTake(SemaMan, Uint32): wait for semaphore with timeout
  void semaDelete(SemaMan): delete a semaphore

Note:
  - SemaMan is actually pointer to SemaObj
  - SemaObj is used both for binary and counting semaphore


